race.comment: Siding with the newcomer MEET ME HALFWAY (12), a filly by Zousain on debut for the Hayes yard. She's won a trial leading in over 750m at Pakenham Synthetic and won't need to be a star to be going close here. WHERE'S MY SOCK (7) has just found one better at her past two, hard in the market last time behind a talented horse at Ballarat. Drawn wide here but she can roll forward and take catching. SMART AND MIGHTY (13) ran a strong race first up at Albury despite going under as favourite, beaten a nose over 900m. Fitter for that and will be very hard to beat. HEGELY (11) has been about the mark in all three runs to date, close up at Kilmore last time over a touch further. Back in trip should suit, she'll be strong in the finish. REDEMPTION TIME (4) has had plenty of chances but could sneak a placing.
